The paper proposes a new algorithm for learning graphical models with a penalty on the cost of inference, specifically arithmetic circuits. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also involves splitting conditional distributions, which is a common technique in data structures (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses experiments on real-world domains, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
